 <text>
  <front>
   <head>GOD Sovereign and Gracious.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">THE Lord! how fearful is his Name?</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">How wide is his Command?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nature with all its Mighty Frame</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Lies rolling in his Hand.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Immortal Glory forms his Throne,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Light his Awful Robe;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whilst with a Smile or with a Frown</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">He manages the Globe.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A Word of His Almighty Breath</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Can swell or sink the Seas;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Build the vast Empires of the Earth,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Or break 'em as he please.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Adoring Angels round him fall</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">In all their Shining Forms,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">His Sovereign Eye looks thro' them all,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And pities Mortal Worms.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">His Bowels to our Worthless Race</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">In sweet Compassion move;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He Cloaths his Looks with softest Grace,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And takes his Title, Love.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Now let the Lord for ever Reign,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Sway us as he will,</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Sick or in Health, in Ease or Pain,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">We are his Favourites still.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No more shall peevish Passion rise,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The Tongue no more Complain;</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis Sovereign Love that lends our Joys,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Love resumes again.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
